	<div class="blog-archive-entries-wrapper">
		<div id="unique-entry-id-445" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Newsround Hotseat</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 22 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>If you have a question for the Captain last week you could have either gone to the VIP section of <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="self">www.vampirates.co.uk/</a> or to Newsround website, as the Captain was in the Hotseat last Friday.  The results have just been published on their website, so please go and check out <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews/hi/newsid_9510000/newsid_9510200/9510212.stm" rel="self">news.bbc.co.uk/cbbcnews</a><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-443" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Penny Smith Chats to Justin Somper</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 18 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Sq_Rackham.jpg" src="Sq_Rackham.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>Radio 2 Arts Show: Penny Smith sits In at chats to Justin Somper at 1:30 / 2:00 - <a href="http://bbc.in/jJXMNY" rel="self">http://bbc.in/jJXMNY</a><br />This should be available abroad and in the UK until 12:02AM Sat, 25 Jun 2011 according to the website.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-441" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Red House - Win Set of Signed Vampirates Books</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 17 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></div>Red house books have just relaunched their website and have added in a couple of competitions. &nbsp;One is winning signed Vampirates books.  Please see <a href="http://www.redhouse.co.uk/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/qs_content1_tbp?storeId=10151&catalogId=10051&langId=100&title=Red%20House%20Competitions&spotName=wl_RHcompetitions" rel="self">http://www.redhouse.co.uk/</a> for more information and to take part.<br /><br />The question is &ldquo;Who is Justin&rsquo;s favourite children&rsquo;s author of all time?&rdquo;<br />Closing date: 11th July 2011<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-434" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">On The Radio</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 16 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Sq_Rackham.jpg" src="Sq_Rackham.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>Don&rsquo;t forget tomorrow that The Captain will be chatting with Claudia Winkleman on BBC Radio 2 on the 17th June from 11.30pm (if you're not quite Nocturnal enough, you'll be able to catch up on BBC iPlayer if you are in the UK).<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-437" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Newsround's Hotseat</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 14 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="scroll" src="scroll.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Justin Somper wrote on Twitter &ldquo;I&rsquo;m in Newsround's Hotseat this week so send in any questions by Friday (17 June) to http://t.co/kvswGF8 &ldquo;<br />Newsround is asking &ldquo;So what would you like to ask Justin?&rdquo;, why don&rsquo;t you drop by and fill in their form.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-433" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Claudia Winkleman on BBC Radio 2</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 10 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Sq_Rackham.jpg" src="Sq_Rackham.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>Justin will be chatting with Claudia Winkleman on BBC Radio 2 on the 17th June from 11.30pm (if you're not quite Nocturnal enough, you'll be able to catch up on BBC iPlayer!)<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-415" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Pirate Quiz</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 03 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>We are off to collect today&rsquo;s Times after reading this from @JustinSomper on twitter.<br />Check out a swashbuckling pirate quiz by yours truly in today's Times (Young Times). Which pirate are you?<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-414" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twittering</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 02 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>The Captain has done it he has got to over 1000 followers on Twitter.  Thank you to everyone who follows him, we did it.<br /><br />If you have not got a twitter account here are some highlights<br />@WarwicKnowledge wrote that was retweeted by @JustinSomper<br />&ldquo;Writing and Publishing Children's Literature with @helenst_ @JustinSomper @sally_nicholls Mal Peet and Leila Rasheed http://bit.ly/k5fKzg&rdquo;<br /><br />and @JustinSomper wrote<br />&ldquo;I&rsquo;ll be at Hanwell Library this Saturday, with @GeeMarks and Frank Cottrell Boyce. Join us and help us to fight to save Hanwell Library!&rdquo;<br />Hanwell Library is on Cherington Rd, London W7 3HL (Just off the A4020 Uxbridge Road in Ealing.)<br /><br />It&rsquo;s a shame my web software is not on the same device as my twitter account, it would be much quicker.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-410" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Vampirates Tours</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 02 June 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Later in June, Justin will be touring around the UK for real on an exciting one week tour through London, Liverpool, Oldham, Lancashire and Cheshire.<br />Don&rsquo;t forget we are 4 days away from the blog tour too.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-412" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter and Blackbeard</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 28 May 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>If you don&rsquo;t follow Justin Somper (@JustinSomper) on Twitter here are some reasons to get a twitter account and follow him.<br /><br />&ldquo;Blackbeard's anchor lifted from Davy Jones's Locker <a href="http://bbc.in/lLUaDP" rel="self">http://bbc.in/lLUaDP</a>&rdquo;<br /><br />&rdquo;Excited to hear they've found Blackbeard's anchor - more than 1000 kg of pirate history!&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;Review of @JustinSomper's Immortal War - A fitting conclusion to the series. Nocturnals get ready!! @simonkids_UK - <a href="http://bit.ly/kVjhzZ" rel="self">http://bit.ly/kVjhzZ</a>&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;@empireofbooks @simonkids_UK Thanks for the first official review of IMMORTAL WAR, Ryan! Couldn't be more thrilled with your verdict.&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;I'm on a mission to have 1000 followers by June 9th - publication day of IMMORTAL WAR. Can you help?&rdquo;<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-407" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Blog Tour</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 25 May 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Blog Tour" src="BlogTour.jpg" width="213" height="539" /></div>So no one is left out here is a copy of the blog tour, set up by the folks at S&S and sent to me by the Captain so everyone gets the chance to see it.<br /><br />Monday 6th June - Chicklish - Extract #1 (<a href="http://keris.typepad.com/chicklet/2011/05/news-vampirates-immortal-war-blog-tour.html" rel="self" title="http://keris.typepad.com/chicklet/2011/05/news-vampirates-immortal-war-blog-tour.html">http://keris.typepad.com/chicklet/</a>)<br />Tuesday 7th June - My Favourite Books - An interview with Justin Somper (<a href="http://myfavouritebooks.blogspot.com/p/blog-tours-2011.html" rel="self" title="http://myfavouritebooks.blogspot.com/p/blog-tours-2011.html">http://myfavouritebooks.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Wednesday 8th June - The Crooked Shelf - The Women of Vampirates (<a href="http://thecrookedshelf.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://thecrookedshelf.blogspot.com/">http://thecrookedshelf.blogspot.com/</a>) (SM I think I cannot find any comment about it).<br />Thursday 9th June - Feeling Fictional - Animal Antics (<a href="http://www.feelingfictional.com/2011/05/news-vampirates-blog-tour-with-justin.html" rel="self" title="http://www.feelingfictional.com/2011/05/news-vampirates-blog-tour-with-justin.html">http://www.feelingfictional.com/</a>)<br />Friday 10th June - The Bookette - Extract #2 (<a href="http://www.thebookette.co.uk/" rel="self" title="http://www.thebookette.co.uk/">http://www.thebookette.co.uk/</a>)<br />Saturday 11th June - Girls Without A Bookshelf - Playlists & The Music of Vampirates (<a href="http://withoutabookshelf.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://withoutabookshelf.blogspot.com/">http://withoutabookshelf.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Sunday 12th June - Wondrous Reads - 10 Ways to Know You're Obsessed with Vampirates (<a href="http://www.wondrousreads.com/2011/05/news-justin-sompers-vampirates-blog.html" rel="self" title="http://www.wondrousreads.com/2011/05/news-justin-sompers-vampirates-blog.html">http://www.wondrousreads.com/</a>)<br />Monday 13th June - Daisy Chain Books - Ending An Era: Killing Off Vampirates (<a href="http://daisychainbookreviews.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://daisychainbookreviews.blogspot.com/">http://daisychainbookreviews.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Tuesday 14th June - Empire of Books - Top ten Vampirates characters ever (<a href="http://empire-of-books.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://empire-of-books.blogspot.com/">http://empire-of-books.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Wednesday 15th June - Book Zone For Boys -- Q&A with Justin (<a href="http://bookzone4boys.blogspot.com/" rel="self" title="http://bookzone4boys.blogspot.com/">http://bookzone4boys.blogspot.com/</a>)<br />Thursday 16th June - I Want To Read That - WIN! Vampirates swag (<a href="http://www.iwanttoreadthat.com/" rel="self" title="http://www.iwanttoreadthat.com/">http://www.iwanttoreadthat.com/</a>)<br /><br />Later in June, Justin will be touring around the UK for real on an exciting one week tour through London, Liverpool, Oldham, Lancashire and Cheshire.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-405" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">BLOG Its up</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 18 May 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>I see Vampirates.co.uk VIP section has now been updated.  There is a new blog by Justin Somper.  I got a mention (very happy here).<br />"I caught up with another valued crew-mate, Ship&rsquo;s Mouse, at the Oxford Literary Festival in April."<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-403" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter Nuggets</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 12 May 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="ImmortalWar.jpg" src="Immortal War.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></div>The Immortal War arrives in Paperback on 9th June 2011 in the UK and as you can see from the tweet below the United States and Canada get theirs six months later.<br /><br />"Looking forward to returning to Warwick Uni for first time in 21 (!) years - to talk at Alumni Knowledge Exchange Day on May 21st."<br /><br />"Thanks for your tweet. IMMORTAL WAR will be published in the US in January 2012."<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-404" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">No Blog Yet.</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 07 May 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>I know I am not finding much at the moment.  I notice even under Stop Press the Vampirates.co.uk staff have written "You Nocturnals are not the only ones starting to wonder!" about the fact Justin Somper has been too busy writing Immortal War to publish a blog.  I think getting my hands on a copy of the book is more important to me, then Grace's Crossing Stories than a blog so I will sit and wait a bit longer.  Only about a month to go.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-400" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 18 April 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Being rather slow ... JustinSomper wrote on Twitter.<br />"Much looking forward to the FCBG conference this weekend? Tweet me if you're going to be there <img class="blog-image-smiley" src="../../../rw_common/plugins/blog/smiley_wink.png" width="21" height="21" alt="Winking" border="0" />"<br />It's the Federation Of Children Book Groups and their conference was over the whole weekend.  I just hope everyone enjoyed themselves.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-397" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Oxford Literary Festival</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 09 April 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><img class="imageStyle" alt="" src="page73_blog_entry397_1.jpg" width="80" height="80" />Justin Somper was at the Oxford Literary Festival today.  My daughter and I had a wonderful day together in Oxford, hunting down our tickets and seeing his show.<br /><br />If you ever get the chance of going to see an author is it well worth it, even if it is just a signing.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-396" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Authors Visiting</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 30 March 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></div>Oxford is enjoying authors visiting over the next few weeks.  This Saturday Anthony Horowitz is visiting Waterstones at one o'clock and the following Saturday Justin Somper will be visiting Corpus Christi College at two o'clock (cost &pound;5) as one of the authors appearing for the Oxford Literary Festival.<br />Please see <a href="http://www.waterstones.com/waterstonesweb/displayDetailEvent.do?searchType=1&author=Anthony|Horowitz" rel="self" title="http://www.waterstones.com/events">www.waterstones.com/</a> and <a href="http://www.oxfordliteraryfestival.com/" rel="self" title="http://www.oxfordliteraryfestival.com/">www.oxfordliteraryfestival.com/</a> for more information.<br /><br />Justin Somper wrote on Twitter "Having a great time at Bologna Book Fair. Great city, loads of sun, fab food, fun crowd AND lots of chances to practice my Italiano!".  So it is not just us fans that enjoy these events.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-395" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Oxford Literary Festival</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 21 March 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Justin Somper wrote on Twitter: <br />"Nice mention in today's Sunday Times of my event at Oxford Literary Festival on April 9th - more info at <a href="http://www.oxfordliteraryfestival.com/" rel="self" title="http://www.oxfordliteraryfestival.com/">www.oxfordliteraryfestival.com/</a>"<br /><br />The 2011 Festival will present the most impressive and prestigious programme yet staged at Oxford - more than 550 speakers over 9 days at Christ Church, Corpus Christi and Merton Colleges.<br />Event 843 is Justin Somper at the Corpus Christi College, on 9th April at 2:00pm, cost of &pound;5, Suitable for 10+ <br />"Justin Somper&rsquo;s high-octane Vampirates sequence, fusing pirate adventure and vampire myth, is published in 34 countries and 24 languages. Anthony Horowitz said of it, &lsquo;Totally original ... I wish I&rsquo;d had this idea!&rsquo;  Hear Justin talk about the world of Vampirates in this highly interactive session, and enjoy a sneak preview of Immortal War, the sixth and final book in the sequence, ahead of its publication in June. Find out more and read Justin&rsquo;s blog, at www.vampirates.co.uk or follow him at www.twitter.com/JustinSomper. <br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-394" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 17 March 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="" src="page73_blog_entry394_1.jpg" width="48" height="48" /></div>Did you know @JustinSomper was on Twitter? here are two of his latest tweets.<br /><br />"Interesting to see that University of Hertfordshire now has a Vampire module on its MA in modern literary studies. Bring it on!"<br /><br />"Great news that the Cutty Sark restoration is moving on and the ship will be open to the public again next Spring. Look forward to visiting."<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-390" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Festival of the Word</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 25 February 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Justin Somper will be attending the OsLitFest on Wednesday 16th March from 3.15-4.30pm at Oswestry Library Arthur St Oswestry, SY11 1JN.  I love the description of the cost "Cost: Free to enjoy - just pop-in to meet Justin."<br /><br />"Justin will be appearing at The Marches School earlier in the day to read and speak with students.  Then, afterwards, come along and meet the author of these well-liked books at Oswestry Library, and even get your book-signed too!"<br /><br />Books must be getting popular again as there seem to be more and more literary festivals or as Oswestry puts it "Festival of the Word".<br />Please see <a href="http://www.thebestof.co.uk/local/oswestry/events/285029/justin-somper-author-of-vampirates" rel="self" title="http://www.thebestof.co.uk/local/oswestry/events/285029/justin-somper-author-of-vampirates">http://www.thebestof.co.uk/local/oswestry/events/285029/justin-somper-author-of-vampirates</a> for more information.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-387" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Hornsey Library in Crouch End</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 01 February 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Justin Somper wrote on twitter that "Next Saturday (Feb 5th) I'll be at Hornsey Library in Crouch End at 2:00 pm to chat and mark National Library Day. Come and say hi!"<br /><br />Sadly I will not be able to make is as it coincides with Chinese New Year celebrations, I hope Cheng Li approves me celebrating the year of the Rabbit instead.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-386" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Catch up</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 27 January 2011 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="ring" src="ring.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Just going though Justin Somper's blog entries, as I have been missing a lot lately and spotted these I thought you might be interested in:<br /><br />"you asked if there will be a VAMPIRATES play? As a matter of fact, I&rsquo;ve just signed a contract with a theatre company who are going to create a VAMPIRATES play to take into schools and festivals. I&rsquo;m excited to see what they come up with. Watch this space for more details on that."<br /><br />"I can&rsquo;t remember where I mentioned that Lorcan has a brother &ndash; possibly during one of my US tour events. But yes he does. His name is Cathal and he&rsquo;s involved in Lorcan&rsquo;s &ldquo;Crossing Story&rdquo;."<br /><br />I always think of Ma Kettle&rsquo;s of being a combination of three places &ndash; the Rover&rsquo;s Return (from UK soap Coronation Street), the Moulin rouge (in Paris) and the Boar&rsquo;s Head Tavern (from Shakespeare&rsquo;s Henry 4th plays). It&rsquo;s a crazy, over-the-top kind of place that changes all the time so I&rsquo;d say just run with your imaginations.<br /><br /></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 

